WEBVTT

00:24.750 --> 00:26.542
<i>[ Man On Radio ]</i>
<i>Unemployment is expected to rise—</i>

00:26.626 --> 00:29.712
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>It was the late '70s,</i>
<i>and everybody was in the middle of it—</i>

00:29.796 --> 00:32.548
<i>of the recession,</i>
<i>the mile-long lines at the station,</i>

00:32.631 --> 00:34.091
<i>the hostage crisis in Iran.</i>

00:36.011 --> 00:39.221
<i>When I look back at it now,</i>
<i>it's amazing I can remember any of it.</i>

00:39.306 --> 00:44.310
<i>It feels like snapshots</i>
<i>from someone else's life,</i>
<i>all connected by one man.</i>

00:50.317 --> 00:52.443
<i>A guy named Steve Rubell</i>
<i>had a dream—</i>

00:52.527 --> 00:55.404
<i>to throw the best damn party</i>
<i>the world had ever seen...</i>

00:55.489 --> 00:57.615
<i>and to make it last forever.</i>

00:57.699 --> 01:01.202
<i>He built a world where fantasy</i>
<i>was offered up as reality,</i>

01:01.286 --> 01:04.622
<i>where an 80-year-old disco queen</i>
<i>could play till dawn,</i>

01:04.706 --> 01:08.918
<i>where models mingled with mechanics,</i>
<i>plumbers danced with princes.</i>

01:09.002 --> 01:12.880
<i>It was a place where all labels</i>
<i>were left behind,</i>

01:12.964 --> 01:15.466
<i>a place where there were no rules.</i>

01:17.677 --> 01:21.222
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>♪ Baby, my heart is full of love ♪</i>

01:21.306 --> 01:23.599
<i>♪ And desire for you ♪</i>

01:23.683 --> 01:27.394
<i>♪ Now come on down and do</i>
<i>what you got to do ♪</i>

01:27.479 --> 01:30.940
<i>♪ You started this fire</i>
<i>down in my soul ♪♪</i>

01:31.024 --> 01:34.485
<i>[ Narrator ] In 1979, I was 19 years old,</i>
<i>and I had nothing.</i>
[ Horns Honking ]

01:35.529 --> 01:38.280
<i>Now, my dad would say</i>
<i>I had more than he did</i>
<i>at my age, but you know what?</i>

01:38.365 --> 01:41.450
<i>To me, fillin' gas tanks</i>
<i>at a Jersey City station,</i>

01:41.535 --> 01:44.662
<i>goin' to the same dingy bar</i>
<i>with the same guys,</i>

01:44.746 --> 01:47.706
<i>tryin' to pick up</i>
<i>on the same chicks</i>
<i>was not tons of fun.</i>

01:47.791 --> 01:51.127
[ Moaning ]

01:51.211 --> 01:55.131
[ Panting ]

01:57.134 --> 02:00.469
I can't believe
you came already.
Sorry.

02:02.681 --> 02:05.141
I'm sorry.

02:05.225 --> 02:09.270
It’s just that—
Look at you. You're so―

02:09.354 --> 02:12.481
You wanna go out tomorrow?
I know this place
where the pizza's dynamite.

02:12.566 --> 02:15.109
[ Zipper Zipping ]
What?

02:15.193 --> 02:18.195
I'm from Montclair, right?

02:18.280 --> 02:21.574
And you're
from Jersey City.
Yeah.

02:21.658 --> 02:25.494
So I don't go out with guys
from Jersey City.

02:25.579 --> 02:27.538
Oh.

02:29.207 --> 02:32.084
<i>[ Narrator ]</i>
<i>I knew the real escape</i>
<i>was right across the river.</i>

02:32.169 --> 02:34.879
<i>But I didn't even have a car.</i>

02:34.963 --> 02:38.841
<i>Even though New York</i>
<i>was three miles away,</i>
<i>it seemed like another world.</i>

02:38.925 --> 02:41.177
<i>I'd been there before</i>
<i>with my mom.</i>

02:41.261 --> 02:45.890
<i>She did makeup for this television show</i>
<i>and took me to work with her a few times.</i>

02:45.974 --> 02:50.394
<i>It was incredible.</i>
<i>Everyone wanted to be around the stars.</i>

02:50.478 --> 02:52.605
<i>My mother always told me</i>
<i>I could be anything I wanted to be,</i>

02:52.689 --> 02:54.607
<i>and I believed her.</i>

02:56.443 --> 02:58.736
<i>Mom died when I was 12.</i>

03:00.614 --> 03:04.200
<i>This was Dad.</i>
<i>His idea of the good life...</i>

03:04.284 --> 03:06.952
<i>was a can of Schlitz</i>
<i>and a Jack Benny special on the tube.</i>

03:07.037 --> 03:10.247
<i>I had to break out.</i>

03:10.332 --> 03:12.917
<i>I knew I had to make a change.</i>

03:15.503 --> 03:17.922
All right, all right, all right!

03:20.091 --> 03:22.051
Move over.
[ Scoffs ]

03:22.135 --> 03:24.136
What?
What you laughin' at?

03:24.221 --> 03:26.222
What's with the hair?
What's that,
the new look?

03:26.306 --> 03:28.891
Look at this guy!
Look at this guy!
Where's my hair?

03:28.975 --> 03:32.937
What are you talkin' about?
[ Laughs ]
You look like Vidal Sassoon.

03:33.021 --> 03:35.022
'‘If you don't look good''―
[ Together ]
'‘We don't look good.''

03:35.106 --> 03:37.149
<i>- ♪♪ [ Disco Beat ]</i>
<i>- ♪ Please don't let me be misunderstood ♪</i>

03:51.164 --> 03:55.292
Shit. I should have borrowed
my brother's platforms.

03:55.377 --> 03:57.586
Do I look short?
No, you look all right.
You gotta fix your collar.

03:57.671 --> 03:59.672
I don't know, man.

03:59.756 --> 04:01.257
You better have put on
new underwear.

04:01.341 --> 04:03.092
Get the fuck outta here!
Hey, you guys.

04:03.176 --> 04:05.177
Hey, you guys.
You guys, you guys.

04:05.262 --> 04:07.805
Before we go in,
check it out.

04:09.391 --> 04:11.558
Oh, take me home, ba―
Who are they?

04:11.643 --> 04:13.686
That one’s Julie Black
from <i>All of My Children.</i>
She's my fuckin' dream girl.

04:13.770 --> 04:17.398
Julie Black— she's from Alpine.
My aunt does her ma's hair.

04:17.482 --> 04:19.440
Saw her once, too,
hangin' out at the Alpine Inn.

04:19.526 --> 04:22.236
Alpine Inn?
We should stake her out.

04:22.320 --> 04:25.281
[ Scoffs ]
Where was this
taken, anyway?

04:25.365 --> 04:27.491
54.

04:27.575 --> 04:30.369
You know, Studio 54.
Ain't you never heard of it?

04:30.453 --> 04:32.371
That place
is full of freaks.
And girls.

04:32.455 --> 04:34.373
And fags.
Come on, you guys.

04:34.457 --> 04:39.086
Listen, you know
who was there last night?
Jacqueline Bisset.

04:39.170 --> 04:41.630
You know who she is?
Yeah, I fucked her.

04:41.715 --> 04:43.841
[ Laughs ]
[ Laughs ]

04:43.925 --> 04:46.844
All right, you turkeys
can stay here and rot,
for all I care,

04:46.928 --> 04:50.014
but I'm gonna go see
if I can get a look at Olivia.

04:50.098 --> 04:51.932
[ Together ]
Olivia Newton-John?

04:52.017 --> 04:53.767
Ow-oooh!
We ain't there yet?

04:53.852 --> 04:58.480
<i>- ♪ B-B-B-Baby, you just</i>
<i>ain't seen nothin' yet ♪</i>
- Fuck you, Jersey!

04:58.565 --> 05:02.359
<i>♪ Here's somethin' that</i>
<i>you're never gonna forget ♪</i>

05:02.444 --> 05:06.238
<i>♪ B-B-B-B-Baby, you just</i>
<i>ain't seen n-n-nothin' yet ♪</i>
[ Horns Honking ]

05:06.323 --> 05:08.657
<i>♪ Listen</i>
<i>You ain't been around ♪</i>
Shit.

05:08.742 --> 05:10.743
We'll save you
a place in line.
Hey, wait!

05:10.827 --> 05:13.162
You moth—
You gonna leave me
here with these freaks?

05:13.246 --> 05:15.748
[ Horns Honking ]
[ Chattering ]

05:17.125 --> 05:22.421
- [ Crowd Clamoring ]
<i>- ♪ B-B-B-B-Baby, you just</i>
<i>ain't seen n-n-nothin' yet ♪</i>

05:22.505 --> 05:26.759
<i>- ♪ Here's somethin', here's somethin'</i>
<i>you're never gonna forget, baby ♪</i>
- [ Man ] Step back.

05:26.843 --> 05:30.012
<i>♪ You know, you know, you know</i>
<i>you just ain't seen nothin' yet ♪♪</i>
[ Together ] Hey!

05:30.096 --> 05:34.600
<i>[ Shane Narrating ]</i>
<i>A lot of people thought the door</i>
<i>was a better show than inside.</i>

05:34.684 --> 05:37.102
<i>People would try anything</i>
<i>to get in.</i>

05:37.187 --> 05:41.273
<i>Marc was the doorman,</i>
<i>but it was Steve Rubell's club</i>
<i>and his door.</i>

05:41.358 --> 05:45.027
I can't let you in here.
You're wearing an ascot.
You look like an asshole.

05:45.111 --> 05:47.780
- [ Both Laugh ]
<i>- [ Shane ]</i>
<i>He was out in front every night...</i>

05:47.864 --> 05:49.531
<i>making sure only</i>
<i>the right people got in.</i>

05:49.616 --> 05:51.825
No. Go home.
Sorry. No.

05:51.910 --> 05:54.119
Hey, come on!
[ Steve ]
Over there.

05:59.000 --> 06:01.752
Excuse me.
He just pointed at us.

06:01.836 --> 06:04.713
Excuse me.
Whoo!

06:04.798 --> 06:06.382
Okay, just you.
What?

06:06.466 --> 06:09.385
Say what?
Just you. Not him.

06:09.469 --> 06:11.387
Ladies―
Hey, man, he's my friend.
You can't―

06:11.471 --> 06:15.015
Girls, please.
Stand back, please.
Step back, please.

06:15.100 --> 06:17.309
Step back.

06:17.394 --> 06:21.397
Oh, my God.
Don't be a spaz, man.
Go for it.

06:21.481 --> 06:23.565
All right, but don't wait for me.
I'll find my way home.

06:23.650 --> 06:25.359
Okay, you guys,
come on.

06:25.443 --> 06:28.237
Hey, I'm gonna slide in here.
[ Whispering ]
Go in, go in.

06:28.321 --> 06:33.242
Please. Hey!
Get your fuckin' hands off me,
you jive-ass turkey!

06:33.326 --> 06:34.868
Big-ass fuckin' gorilla!

06:34.953 --> 06:37.454
Fuck you!
Sorry, guy.

06:37.539 --> 06:40.082
[ Woman ]
Steve! Hey, Steve!
What?

06:40.166 --> 06:42.835
Not with that shirt.
[ Scoffs ]

06:44.295 --> 06:45.671
Hey!

06:45.755 --> 06:47.840
I said not with that shirt.

06:49.884 --> 06:51.844
[ Man In Crowd ]
That's your ticket in, man.

06:58.560 --> 07:01.603
[ Crowd Cheering ]

07:05.191 --> 07:07.943
[ Woman In Crowd ]
You're hot!

07:08.027 --> 07:11.363
[ Man In Crowd ]
That's how you get in.
Welcome to my party, handsome.

07:13.324 --> 07:16.118
[ Friend ]
Go for it, Shane!

07:16.202 --> 07:18.412
<i>[ Shane Narrating ]</i>
<i>He chose me.</i>

07:18.496 --> 07:20.289
<i>I'd never been chosen for anything before.</i>

07:20.373 --> 07:22.791
<i>♪♪ [ Disco, Muffled ]</i>

07:32.760 --> 07:34.303
You wanna check
that bod, sugar?

07:35.346 --> 07:37.014
[ Giggles ]

07:38.057 --> 07:41.143
- [ Both Laughing ]
- Whoo!

07:43.396 --> 07:45.772
<i>♪♪ [ Disco ]</i>

07:51.070 --> 07:55.073
[ Crowd Chattering ]

08:18.014 --> 08:20.891
[ Woman ]
Belushi does this
crazy samurai guy.

08:37.116 --> 08:39.034
[ Man ]
Kiss me.

08:39.118 --> 08:40.494
[ Moans ]

08:46.626 --> 08:49.044
[ Moaning ]

09:14.821 --> 09:17.739
[ Woman Laughing,
Moaning ]

09:27.500 --> 09:31.420
<i>- [ Thunder Crashes, Music Stops ]</i>
- Mirror, mirror on the wall.

09:31.504 --> 09:33.922
Who's the fairest of them all?

09:34.007 --> 09:37.175
Truman? Truman Capote,
where are you?

09:37.260 --> 09:40.929
Here, sugar!
[ Laughs ]
There you are.

09:41.014 --> 09:44.349
In honor of the fantastic
new face lift,

09:44.434 --> 09:48.645
I thought I'd get you
a couple of things.
[ Chuckles ]

09:48.730 --> 09:53.108
- [ Steve Chuckling ]
- [ Audience Laughing ]

10:01.075 --> 10:02.868
[ Chuckles ]

10:05.204 --> 10:08.957
And― And to make sure
that the lift sticks,

10:09.042 --> 10:12.377
I thought we should all
'‘knock on wood.''

10:12.462 --> 10:15.964
<i>[ Explosion ]</i>
<i>♪♪ [ ‘‘Knock On Wood'' ]</i>

