[ Chorus ]
♪ Think I better knock, knock
knock on wood ♪

11:49.142 --> 11:52.811
♪ Think I better knock, knock
knock on wood ♪♪

11:56.607 --> 11:58.734
Well, the thing about stars
is they're short.

11:58.818 --> 12:00.736
You talk to any of'em?
Kind of.

12:00.820 --> 12:02.738
Like who?
Who?

12:02.822 --> 12:05.574
Like— I don't know,
but you should have seen
all the photographers.

12:05.658 --> 12:08.034
I bet you I even got
in one of their pictures.

12:08.119 --> 12:10.871
Think Farrah
ever goes there?
Maybe.

12:10.955 --> 12:12.914
And Lee Majors?
Probably.

12:12.999 --> 12:15.584
- What about Princess Grace?
- Sure, I bet she goes all the time.

12:15.668 --> 12:18.253
Really? Maybe we can
touch her when she goes by.

12:18.337 --> 12:20.672
And we'll tell her that Mom
named us after her.
[ Man ] Hey, kids!

12:20.757 --> 12:22.591
Hey, Dad.

12:22.675 --> 12:27.262
- What?
- Hey, Dad, can I borrow
the keys tonight?

12:27.346 --> 12:29.973
What for?
Shane was in the city last night,
and he wants to go back.

12:30.057 --> 12:33.477
The city?
Yeah, Shane was just
telling us...

12:33.561 --> 12:36.104
how he went to Studio 54
last night.

12:36.189 --> 12:39.608
Studio 54?
That's that big disco
everybody's talking about.

12:39.692 --> 12:42.110
Where all the stars go.
Yeah, Dad,
you shoulda seen it.

12:42.195 --> 12:44.446
Hey, I saw a star once―
Bob Hope.

12:44.530 --> 12:47.324
Did you see him there?
[ Laughs ]

12:47.408 --> 12:50.786
Thanks for the memories, Dad,
but it wasn't a Korean War show.

12:50.870 --> 12:51.953
Yeah.

13:01.589 --> 13:04.758
- What else, Shane?
- Well, I went up into the balcony.

13:04.842 --> 13:06.802
It was pretty―

13:10.389 --> 13:13.058
It was pretty... dark.

13:21.067 --> 13:23.235
<i>[ Crowd Shouting ]</i>

13:28.282 --> 13:30.242
[ Snoring ]

13:51.556 --> 13:53.265
<i>[ Shane Narrating ]</i>
<i>The girl who cut my hair</i>
<i>had this boyfriend...</i>

13:53.349 --> 13:55.892
<i>whose sister did the books for Steve Rubell</i>
<i>and got me an interview.</i>

13:57.270 --> 14:02.858
<i>Steve Rubell, a regular Brooklyn kid</i>
<i>who got his start by running</i>
<i>a few steak houses,</i>

14:02.942 --> 14:04.401
<i>was now on top of the world.</i>

14:04.485 --> 14:06.194
He's right out there in the hallway
if you want to see him for yourself.

14:06.279 --> 14:09.739
He's gorgeous?
He's gorgeous.
Look for yourself.

14:09.824 --> 14:12.200
<i>I was warned</i>
<i>that Steve didn't hire any dummies,</i>

14:12.285 --> 14:15.787
<i>and I should be on my toes</i>
<i>because he could ask some</i>
<i>really tricky questions.</i>

14:15.872 --> 14:18.123
What's two plus two?
Huh?

14:18.207 --> 14:21.668
You'll be fine.
You're right, he's gorgeous.

14:21.752 --> 14:24.588
Come on in.

14:24.672 --> 14:27.549
Where do bad little bartenders go
if they don't go to hell first?

14:27.633 --> 14:30.760
[ All ] Xenon.
Right. A fate worse than death.

14:30.845 --> 14:36.558
So, as of tonight,
the new bartender will be...

14:37.977 --> 14:41.062
Rhett.
Choice.

14:41.147 --> 14:44.065
Oh, and we got a new busboy.
His name is Shane.

14:44.150 --> 14:47.152
Shane! Shane, come here,
come here.

14:48.654 --> 14:51.656
[ Group Laughs ]
[ Steve Chuckles ]

14:51.741 --> 14:54.409
Couldn't find the right size.

14:54.493 --> 14:58.914
And remember, it's you boys
who are truly...

14:58.998 --> 15:00.999
New York's finest.

15:02.168 --> 15:05.003
One Chablis.
Hey, kid!

15:07.340 --> 15:11.343
- Chablis.
- So, uh, what'll it be?

15:12.637 --> 15:15.472
What'll it be?
[ Chuckles ]

15:15.556 --> 15:17.849
Where did they get you, Rocky?
Philadelphia?

15:17.934 --> 15:20.018
No talkin' to the animals, busboy.

15:20.102 --> 15:22.228
Hang in there, baby.

15:25.316 --> 15:28.026
Greg, man, can you
help me please?

15:28.110 --> 15:30.111
This is how it works.

15:30.196 --> 15:32.614
<i>Keep the bottles</i>
<i>and the glasses</i>
<i>off the dance floor.</i>

15:32.698 --> 15:35.700
<i>Now, remember, keep</i>
<i>the champagne cold</i>
<i>and keep it flowing.</i>

15:35.785 --> 15:37.494
<i>You gotta pay attention</i>
<i>to the V.I.P. area.</i>

15:37.578 --> 15:40.288
<i>Steve doesn't want 'em ever to have</i>
<i>to pour champagne themselves.</i>

15:40.373 --> 15:42.624
Now, listen up.

15:42.708 --> 15:45.543
After everybody's all gone,
you check the banquettes.

15:45.628 --> 15:47.963
We usually find
some pretty good stuff.

15:48.047 --> 15:50.632
Is that Julie Black?

15:50.716 --> 15:53.718
Think so.
Ready?
Yeah.

15:53.803 --> 15:57.138
<i>[ Shane Narrating ]</i>
<i>There she was—Julie Black.</i>

15:57.223 --> 16:01.810
<i>Man, she looked even better</i>
<i>in person than on TV.</i>

16:01.894 --> 16:04.479
<i>She was from Jersey, too,</i>
<i>and she'd made it.</i>

16:09.902 --> 16:13.989
You know, I really
gotta get outta here
and get some sleep.

16:14.073 --> 16:17.534
<i>Stevie knew that we have</i>
<i>no royalty in this country—</i>
<i>we have celebrity.</i>

16:17.618 --> 16:21.079
<i>If he could provide</i>
<i>the opportunity for regular people</i>
<i>to dance and bump with the famous,</i>

16:21.163 --> 16:23.331
<i>Studio would be one of a kind.</i>

16:23.416 --> 16:26.084
<i>And I was such a dumb kid.</i>
<i>I mean, all these famous people,</i>

16:26.168 --> 16:29.004
<i>and I didn't know</i>
<i>who any of them were,</i>
<i>and they'd all go,</i>

16:29.088 --> 16:33.049
<i>‘‘Truman! Oh, Truman!''</i>
<i>and I'd be thinkin',</i>
<i>‘‘Who the fuck is Truman?''</i>

16:33.134 --> 16:36.052
Hey, Fiorucci!
How are you?

16:36.137 --> 16:38.680
You know, I'm such
a big fan of yours.
Your windows are great.

16:38.764 --> 16:40.682
<i>Grazie.</i>
Thank you.
Great.

16:40.766 --> 16:42.100
<i>Grazie molto.</i>

16:42.184 --> 16:45.228
[ Speaking Italian ]

16:45.312 --> 16:48.690
You're so Italian and adorable.
I wanna eat you with a spoon.

16:49.942 --> 16:51.860
